\noindent{According to R, I get $\esph{y^1_i|y^B_i=\bar{y}}=$\Sexpr{y1.bary.pred} and $\esph{y_i^0|y_i^B=\bar{y}}=$\Sexpr{y0.bary.pred}, so the estimated TT is $\hat{\Delta^{y}_{RDDOLS}}=$\Sexpr{delta.y.rddols}.\\
Then I calculate $\bm{TT(z)}$ with the following formula:\\}

\centerline{$\Delta^y_{TT}(\bar{z}) = \bar{\alpha} + \theta\bar{\mu}+\theta\displaystyle\frac{\sigma^2_{\mu}}{\sigma^2_{\mu}+\sigma^2_{U}}(\bar{y}-\bar{\mu})$}

